    <!-- Rules Screen -->
    <string name="game_rules">Game Rules</string>
    <string name="rules_text">X-O GAME RULES\n\n1. The game is played on a 3x3 grid.\n\n2. Player 1 uses X, Player 2 uses O.\n\n3. Players take turns placing their symbol in an empty cell.\n\n4. The first player to get 3 of their symbols in a row (horizontally, vertically, or diagonally) wins.\n\n5. If all 9 cells are filled and no player has 3 in a row, the game is a draw.\n\n6. A tournament consists of multiple rounds.\n\n7. The player with the most wins at the end of the tournament is the champion.\n\n8. You can play against AI with 3 difficulty levels: Easy, Medium, Hard.\n\n9. Tournament results are automatically saved and can be viewed in Scores section.</string>

